DAY 1

to check user have admin rights 

- win + R
    - lusrmgr.msc - local user management
    - groups → administrators
    - → dotnet_trng → ebs_bench_2023 → all trainee info
- from desktop - network → view → search active directory → group name
- mstsc - open remote desktop connection from cmd
- appwiz.cpl - app wizard (control panel)
- sysdm.cpl - system properties (environmental variable)
- two type of installation
    - silence
    - attentive
- java path - c :\program file\java\jdk-1.8 (java home)
    - c :\program file\java\jdk-1.8\bin (java path)

ODI Admin (DAY - 1 things covered)

1. All Software Information.
2. 
3. java installation
    1. Remote desktop Connection or laptop
    2. need admin rights
    3. java(open and oracle JDK)
        1. Oracle JDK - 64 bit version 1.8_401
        2. Installation of java
        3. create JAVA_HOME
        4. set JAVA PATH
        5. check java version : java -version
4. 
5. Environment variable
    1. create JAVA_HOME  (case sensitive in linux infra)
        1. system properties → advanced 
            1. environment variables
            2. system variables
                1. new
                    1. variable name: JAVA_HOME
                    2. variable value:   browse directory → c :\program file\java\jdk-1.8
                    3. ok
        2. check if the variable declared correctly 
            1. CMD reads the variable before launch
                1. echo %JAVA_HOME%
    2. Edit PATH (case sensitive)
        1. advance → 
            1. environment variable
            2. system variables 
                1. edit 
                    1. new - browse :c :\program file\java\jdk-1.8\bin (java path) → move up
                    2. ok
                2. ok
        2. check the if the PATH specified correctly 
            1. echo %PATH%
    3. check for java in cmd (interpreter)
        1. CMD → java -version
    4. variables in linux are separated by :
    5. and in variables are separated by ;
    

JAVA Installation (attentive mode)

1. copy Setup(from ccd) to desktop 
    1. run as admin → yes
    2. next → 
        1. default path → c :\program file\java\jdk-1.8\.  can change the path
        2. select all 3 icon → drop down → select this feature and all sub feature will be installed on local hard drive 
        3. next
    3. next 
    4. close.